-- JinkoSolar Gets $58 Million Loan From China Development Bank
-- B y   M a r c   R o c a
-- 2013-04-04T09:10:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-04/jinkosolar-gets-58-million-loan-from-china-development-bank.html
JinkoSolar Holding Co. Ltd. said it
signed an agreement with China  Development Bank  Corp. for a 360
million  yuan  ($58 million) loan to support its domestic
photovoltaic projects.  The loan agreement is for a 15-year period, JinkoSolar said
in a statement on PR Newswire today.  “Securing long-term and stable source of capital, within
this agreement, will reinforce our competitive status and
already leadership position in the Chinese market,” said Xiande
Li, chairman of JinkoSolar. “It demonstrates CDB’s trust in the
company’s strong balance sheet.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marc Roca in London at 
